# AI Agent Guardrails & Guidelines

## CRITICAL: Server Restart Policy
You are strictly FORBIDDEN from telling the user to "test out the changes" you made to any backend Python files or frontend HTML/JS files without First RESTARTING the server or explicitly instructing the user to restart it.

The server does NOT use hot-reloading for its core application logic (`app.py`, `agent.py`, `models.py`, `templates/index.html`, etc.). 

If you make a change, it will NOT take effect until the process running on port 8001 is killed and restarted.

**Protocol for Testing Changes:**
1. If you implemented a fix, you must restart the server using: `lsof -t -i :8001 | xargs kill -9 && bash run.sh` (or appropriately kill the active process).
2. ONLY AFTER the server is freshly started can you tell the user that the changes are ready to test.

Violating this rule causes extreme confusion for the user, as they will be testing stale code.
